HEADWORD: Anagoge
<hw>An`a*go"ge</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
leading up; <?/ + <?/ a leading, <?/ to lead.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
elevation of mind to things celestial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The spiritual meaning or application; esp. the
application of the types and allegories of the Old Testament to subjects
of the New.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

